window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Instantly discover what's <i>really</i> going on around you!</b> </p> <p>Know the truth before you ever hear a word! </p> <p>Approximately 80% of communication is expressed nonverbally. When you know how to unlock the secrets of people's nonverbal cues, you'll always have the upper hand in any situation. </p> <p>In <i>The Power of Body Language</i>, former FBI counterintelligence officer and recognized global expert on nonverbal behavior Joe Navarro teaches you how to \"speed-read\" people: decode sentiments and behaviors, avoid hidden pitfalls, and look for revealing behaviors. You will discover: </p> <p></p> <ul> <li>How the subconscious limbic system drives all body language. </li> <li>Why the face is the least likely place to gauge a person's true feelings. </li> <li>What thumbs, feet, and a simple handshake reveal about moods and motives. </li> <li>The most powerful behaviors that reveal our confidence and true sentiments. </li> <li>Simple nonverbals that instantly establish trust and communicate authority. </li> <li>Why things taught about nonverbals in the '70s and '80s are incorrect. </li> <li>And more! </li> </ul> <p></p>"; 
